    • Field Detail

      • contentType

        public java.lang.String contentType
        The content type of the response. This defaults to "text/html".

      • cookies

        public RecordToken cookies
        All cookies from the setCookies port plus the Cookies from the HttpRequest. Values provided on the setCookies port override values from the HttpRequest for cookies with the same name. (I.e., the model developer wants to replace the cookie on the client with the cookie provided on the input port.)

      • hasNewCookies

        public boolean hasNewCookies
        A flag indicating that new cookies have been received on the setCookies port, and that all cookies should be written to the HttpServletResponse in the doGet() or doPost() method. It would not be wrong to always write the cookies to every HttpServletResponse, but it would be inefficient.

      • headers

        public RecordToken headers
        Headers to include in the response, if any.

      • response

        public java.lang.String response
        The text of the response.

      • statusCode

        public int statusCode
        Status code of the response.
